website_summaries.verdict: Canned food can be a little pricey, but this formula tastes great for both adult dogs and puppies.
pros: Promotes lean muscle development for all ages of dogs with plenty of natural protein in the recipe
Uses a variety of natural foods for overall health
Works equally well as a standalone food or as a tasty topper for dry dog food
cons: Some dogs may not digest canned food as well as dry food

customer_reviews.title: Wet food for a picky eater at a reasonable price!
customer_reviews.text: I use about 1/4 of a can per feeding mixed in with water-wetted dry kibble to entice my picky eater pup. She seems to think it's 100% better with a little extra effort we put in with the wet food, and her coat has gotten thicker, softer, and doesn't seem to shed as much. On top of that, she actually wags her tail for her food now! Is a little of this food doing all of these things? It could be a coincidence, but just in case it isn't, I'm sticking with this addition to her diet. For anyone that's curious, her dry kibble is Diamonds Natural all stages chicken and rice.
customer_reviews.author: Usakiia

customer_reviews.title: I think I got a bad batch.
customer_reviews.text: I have one of the pickiest labradoodles evvvver. She was born on Diamond. She literally ran out of the room and spits it out when I gave it to her. I rolled up little meatballs and nada, nothing. I mixed it with her normal dry food and wouldn’t touch it. She looked at me like I was giving her something bad. Not sure if I got a bad batch or what.
customer_reviews.author: P

customer_reviews.title: Made dog vomit
customer_reviews.text: I bought these because my dog already eats the hard food in this brand, but i must've got a bad batch. There's lil white dots in the food that i don't think is supposed to be there and i have only fed this to my dog 3 times because everyday that he has eaten it he vomits it all up a couple hours later. So, what a waste of 9 other cans that i can't use because something's not right with the food.
customer_reviews.author: melbsnrn

customer_reviews.title: Winner on quality and price.
customer_reviews.text: This food is highly rated on a pet food review site, my dogs like it, and it's very reasonably priced compared to similarly rated dog foods. It is less attractive from a human perspective, with dated-looking packaging, an ingredient list that's not bottom-loaded with trendy superfoods and a frankly less appealing look than some of the chunky vegetable rich canned foods I've purchased. I swear, some days my dogs food looks better than mine. This food is simple, inexpensive and rich in quality meats. Besides, it's easy to add some vegetables on top if you want your dogs to eat more superfoods.
customer_reviews.author: Jared E. Hayter
